OL,3,CInfluencers charged over promoting
OL,4,Cunauthorised financial investments
OL,6,FThe FCA alleges that between May 2018
OL,7,Fand April 2021, Emmanuel Nwanze, aged
OL,8,F30, and Holly Thompson, 33, used an
OL,9,Finstagram account under the handle
OL,10,F@holly fxtrends to provide advice on
OL,11,Fbuying and selling investments called
OL,12,Fcontracts for difference (CFDs),
OL,13,Fwithout authorisation from the
OL,14,Fregulator to do so.
OL,16,FThe FCA also alleges that Mr Nwanze
OL,17,Fpaid the nine social media influencers
OL,18,Fto promote the instagram account to
OL,19,Ftheir combined 4.5 million followers.
